## Mandatory QA Before Session Return

Before returning the session to the user (i.e., before considering any implementation task complete), you **MUST** run tests and QA checks — both **server-side** and **client-side** — to verify with 100% confidence that:

1. All implemented features work correctly and perform everything they are required to do.
2. No errors, regressions, or issues were introduced.

**This is non-negotiable.** Do not mark a task as done or return control to the user until verification is complete. If automated tests exist, run them. If not, perform manual verification (API calls, config validation, log inspection, UI checks, etc.) appropriate to the scope of the change.

